reviews.review_text: Baba Au Rhum is a wonderful cafe with amazing breakfast and brunch options. I tried their omelette and pasta, and both were absolutely delicious! The juice was super refreshing, a perfect addition to the meal. I went there for brunch, and the vibes were just incredible. The combination of trance music and great food made the experience so enjoyable. The ambiance is cozy and laid-back, surrounded by greenery, making it a great spot to relax and unwind. Itâ€™s definitely a place Iâ€™d recommend for a chilled-out brunch in Goa!

This place was one of the best places to eat in Goa when I visited it last year but their taste has gone down.
I had ordered Pizza, white sauce Pasta,vanilla in house ice cream and tomato soup.

The tomato soup was not as good as it was last time, it was too sour

The Pasta was very bland

The Pizza was okay okay

The inhouse ice cream was the same as we would get in the local shop nothing different.

It's a good place to visit but it's your luck if you get good taste food or not
